    {
      "instruction": "<p>Put a large <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined baking tray (or two!) in the oven to heat up (this will stop the pide bottoms from going soggy!)</p><p>Add your <strong>dried</strong> <strong>yeast</strong> to a large bowl with 100ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[150ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[200ml] </span><strong>warm water </strong>and 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[2 tsp]</span> <strong>sugar</strong></p><p>Mix it all together and set aside for 5-10 min for the yeast to develop</p>",
